### Migrating RxDB Attachments with Strategies

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/migration-schema.md

This example shows how to define `migrationStrategies` for RxDB collections to manage attachments during schema migrations. It illustrates three common scenarios: preserving all attachments, removing all attachments, and updating the data of a specific attachment. The `createBlob` utility is used for creating new attachment data.

```javascript
import { createBlob } from 'rxdb';
const migrationStrategies = {
      1: async function(oldDoc){
        // Keep all attachments
        return oldDoc;
      },
      2: async function(oldDoc){
        // Delete all attachments
        oldDoc._attachments = {};
        return oldDoc;
      },
      3: async function(oldDoc){
        // Update data of a single attachment
        oldDoc._attachments.myFile.data = await createBlob(
          'my new text',
          oldDoc._attachments.myFile.content_type
        );
        return oldDoc;
      }
}
```

