### Manual RxDB Collection Migration with State Observation

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/migration-schema.md

This snippet demonstrates how to disable automatic migration on collection creation and manually initiate and monitor the migration process. It shows how to check if a migration is needed, start it with a specified batch size, and subscribe to the migration state observable to provide user feedback. Dependencies include RxDB and a defined collection schema.

```javascript
const messageCol = await myDatabase.addCollections({
  messages: {
    schema: messageSchemaV1,
    autoMigrate: false, // <- migration will not run at creation
    migrationStrategies: {
      1: async function(oldDoc){
        ... // Custom migration logic
        return oldDoc;
      }
    }
  }
});

// check if migration is needed
const needed = await messageCol.migrationNeeded();
if(needed === false) {
  return;
}

// start the migration
messageCol.startMigration(10); // 10 is the batch-size

const migrationState = messageCol.getMigrationState();

// 'start' the observable
migrationState.$.subscribe({
    next: state => console.dir(state),
    error: error => console.error(error),
    complete: () => console.log('done')
});

// Example emitted states:
// {
//     status: 'RUNNING', 
//     count: { total: 50, handled: 0, percent: 0 }
// }
```

