### RxDB: Observing All Migration States

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/migration-schema.html

Explains how to use `RxDatabase.migrationStates()` to get an Observable that emits the migration states of all collections within a database. This is useful for displaying a global migration loading status, especially when collections are added dynamically.

```javascript
const allStatesObservable = myDatabase.migrationStates();
allStatesObservable.subscribe(allStates => {
  allStates.forEach(migrationState => {
    console.log(
      'migration state of ' +
      migrationState.collection.name
    );
  });
});
```

