### RxDB: Refactor data-migrator strategies

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/orga/before-next-major.md

Refactor the RxDB data-migrator to adopt a more flexible strategy definition, similar to WatermelonDB. This involves introducing explicit `toVersion` and `fromVersion` fields within migration strategies, allowing for direct version jumps and improving performance.

```typescript
interface MigrationStrategy {
    // Current approach uses array index as toVersion, which is confusing.
    // Example of current strategy:
    // {
    //     1: (oldDoc) => {
    //         // migrate to version 1
    //         return oldDoc;
    //     }
    // }

    // Proposed approach:
    toVersion: number;
    fromVersion?: number; // Optional, for direct jumps
    migrate: (oldDoc: any, version: number) => Promise<any> | any;
}

// Example of new migration configuration:
// const migrations = {
//     strategies: [
//         {
//             toVersion: 1,
//             migrate: (oldDoc) => {
//                 // migrate to version 1
//                 return oldDoc;
//             }
//         },
//         {
//             toVersion: 3,
//             fromVersion: 1, // Jump from version 1 directly to 3
//             migrate: (oldDoc) => {
//                 // migrate from version 1 to 3
//                 return oldDoc;
//             }
//         }
//     ]
// };
```

